commit_message:
Added missing configuration to horizon docker template.

Added missing copy and link commands:
 && cp -r /horizon/openstack_dashboard /usr/share/openstack-dashboard/ \
 && cp /horizon/openstack_dashboard/local/local_settings.py.example \
     /etc/openstack-dashboard/local_settings \
 && ln -s /etc/openstack-dashboard/local_settings \
     /usr/share/openstack-dashboard/openstack_dashboard/local/local_settings.py \
 && cp /horizon/manage.py /usr/share/openstack-dashboard \
 && python /usr/share/openstack-dashboard/manage.py collectstatic --noinput \

Changed 'mkdir -p /usr/share/openstack-dashboard/static' to 'mkdir -p /usr/share/openstack-dashboard'

Change-Id: Ia79c43d771ab2b3628112a9c4d0e6bb2d3348f4f
Closes-Bug: 1487028

MemoryUnit Incorrectly normalizes to uppercase

Validating scalar unit size and if not followed GNU standard,
converting given scalar unit to GNU standard value after displaying
a warning message.

commit_message:
Increase the concurrency of software-config functional test

The test now creates up to 10 deployments in various stack/deployment
resource combinations and asserts that the resulting server metadata
has the appropriate number of resources.

This test now creates a deployment via OS::Heat::SoftwareDeployments as
the extra nested stack is required to trigger the race causing bug #1477329

Related-Bug: #1477329
Change-Id: Id3d5b09def6d03bca669c1ab0751641b72f61ce4

Galera logs by default to /var/log/mysql_logs these logs are being

This patch adds an option to set the log_directory specifically inside

commit_message:
Allow a log dir that isn't the "service_name"

Galera logs by default to /var/log/mysql_logs these logs are being
ignored and not mounted properly on the host server, because the
service_name that is used to mount the log directory is "galera" and not
"mysql_logs".

This patch adds an option to set the log_directory specifically inside
the env.d yml files, but defaults to "service_name" when the
log_directory option isn't set. This will mean functionality remains
unchanged for all services.

Additionally, the log_directory has changed to "mysql_logs" for galera
containers, to resolve the galera log issue.

Change-Id: I18400248da455156dbba31b9c2ff254b58c51673
Closes-Bug: #1486955
(cherry picked from commit f77cc7a861117b5fe1a0993bd848b26cd47a385a)

commit_message:
Add dlt media to tx_mgr

This change set adds the deletion of the VM vOpt to the transaction
manager.  This helps with the mass concurrent delete flow.  It speeds up
the delete and enables for more resiliancy.

commit_message:
freezer-agent support for keystone v2.0 and v3

The freezer-agent now supports authentication using keystone
versions 2.0 and 3.

Adds the folllowing cli parameter:

  --os-identity-api-version <version>

which is intended to take the place of the deprecated --os-auth-ver
The identity api version can be passed using the environ variable:

  OS_IDENTITY_API_VERSION

Implements blueprint: agent-identity-api-version

Change-Id: Ia9a299d379acccfffc62bd6112fd533d176ac66c

To make sure we don't use the ssl-hello-chk option set by the
puppet-haproxy module we used to redefine the listener options
for all listeners.

With this change a default for the options hash is provided to
the puppet class instead.

commit_message:
Remove httpchk option from haproxy listeners

To make sure we don't use the ssl-hello-chk option set by the
puppet-haproxy module we used to redefine the listener options
for all listeners.

With this change a default for the options hash is provided to
the puppet class instead.

This change also configures use of tcpka only where wanted, as
documented by [1], removing it from the haproxy defaults section,
given it wasn't used anyway by the other listeners which were
indeed overriding options.

1. https://github.com/beekhof/osp-ha-deploy/blob/master/pcmk/lb.scenario

Change-Id: Ic8deb77533f561cea7ce7db1d20f6be5e2dc0d33

commit_message:
Authentication URLs and endpoint clarity re-factor

Admin endpoint is used to build os-url as fail back when they're no others
URL available for authenticating. The legacy code was confusing and entangled between
endpoint discovery and auth_url and os_url (service token) assignments.
This brings better readability with:
- Re-factors by clearly separating url and endpoints methods.
- Makes sure the API version is present when using the service_url (os-url) for
user password validation.

Change-Id: Ibca33c38e78d4b26c7b842d8b7d97db46c3c9734

(not including source, timestamp, metadata).

commit_message:
Introduce Guru Meditation Reports into Ceilometer

This commit integrates functionality from the `openstack.common.report`
module into Ceilometer. This enables Ceilometer services to receive
SIGUSR1 and print a Guru Meditation Report to stderr or file.
The required modules were added to 'openstack-common.conf' as well.

commit_message:
lxc: fix disk_info passed to _create_domain_and_network in _hard_reboot

Commit a7a0b4e542a65b3ba3650db2b7560eb587b9606c changed
_get_instance_disk_info to return a list rather than a json string.  As
part of that, it overwrote the local disk_info variable (which was a
dict) in _hard_reboot before it was passed to
_create_domain_and_network.  Eventually when disk_info gets down to
_create_domain_setup_lxc it fails the _is_booted_from_volume because
it's a list rather than a dict.

This moves the _get_instance_disk_info call in _hard_reboot within the
context.auth_token block since the return value is otherwise not needed,
and creates a unique local variable for the instance disk_info so it
doesn't collide with the disk_info that comes back from
blockinfo.get_disk_info.

At some point we should create objects for these various disk_info
variables because otherwise it's really confusing trying to track the
types and usage of all of these different things called 'disk_info'
which are sometimes dicts and sometimes lists of dicts.

Closes-Bug: #1370590

Co-Authored-By: Andrew Melton <andrew.melton@rackspace.com>

Change-Id: Idba5f1ec3a39b8745b6808df8731ba2ffc160898

commit_message:
Fix "{}" is not a list error for json parameter type

If json paramter `default` of nested stack is set to
[], it resets it to {} and nested resource validations
fail. This patch fixes it by allowing empty list to
passthrough.

Change-Id: I153e9a94566679c01d6ca21713233e3140769ded
Closes-Bug: #1486778

commit_message:
Unauthed tests for Secret & Container ACLs

These tests will attempt CRUD operations on Secret and Container ACLs
without valid tokens. They should all return HTTP 401s. Also added
PATCH support to the common client, and use_auth parameters to ACL
behaviors.

Change-Id: Ie753b6605ae81202a4bb473dd6f9101919f4eda5

commit_message:
Add an explicit test failure condition when auth_token is missing

If the loop exits "successfully" without finding auth_token, scope fall
through would result in 'extension' containing the last iteration of the
'for' loop.

This change results in that behavior explicitly failing with better
error feedback.

Change-Id: Ifa63a78d267e810fcf4adb40524613d7d8f3b5b7
(cherry picked from commit bd742151ba7f5834dc50ea1534e93040eb46aa84)

commit_message:
Add an explicit test failure condition when auth_token is missing

If the loop exits "successfully" without finding auth_token, scope fall
through would result in 'extension' containing the last iteration of the
'for' loop.

This change results in that behavior explicitly failing with better
error feedback.

Change-Id: Ifa63a78d267e810fcf4adb40524613d7d8f3b5b7
(cherry picked from commit bd742151ba7f5834dc50ea1534e93040eb46aa84)

commit_message:
Set keystone under apache mod_wsgi to MPM 6x3

This sets keystone under apache WSGI to MPM mode
limited to 6 worker processess and 3 threads
in order to share info regarding memcached
backends between the threads as well as provide
the optimal performance for high load.

This should allow us to decrease retry for
dead memcache backends and thus fix a
couple of bugs introduced by changes
that are related to multiple processes
of keystone checking memcached backends.

Partial-bug: #1480153
Related-bug: #1471318
Related-bug: #1479782

Change-Id: I01e2c74f8881d4fc208758455b6c13b64f2176c7
Co-Authored-By: Vladimir Kuklin <vkuklin@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Fix list_opts test to not check all deps

The list_opts entrypoint test failed unnecessarily when the
dependencies in the packages were inconsistent. This test doesn't
need to verify that the dependencies are consistent, only that the
entrypoint is available and provides the expected function.

For the backport, I added stevedore to test-requirements.txt
because it's not in requirements.txt already.

Change-Id: I857222e0637b09f45352d9cabbdc5cac8e4fd562

commit_message:
Fix list_opts test to not check all deps

The list_opts entrypoint test failed unnecessarily when the
dependencies in the packages were inconsistent. This test doesn't
need to verify that the dependencies are consistent, only that the
entrypoint is available and provides the expected function.

For the backport, I needed to remove the stevedore additions to
test-requirements-py3.txt and test-requirements.txt because
stevedore is already in requirements.txt.

commit_message:
Split DRIVER_TABLES in external.py

Split DRIVER_TABLES into separate lists for each driver.
This is needed for easier implementation of ModelMigrationSyncTest
in driver/plugin repositoties that were split out from Neutron.

Related-bug: #1470678

Change-Id: Id4558f2230f42377be1dd4f319a2c97122d1fa9d

commit_message:
Dump running WSGI threads before shutdown for testing

In some grenade tests, we hit cinder-api service shutdown
failures. To debug the failures, this patch dumps stack traces
for running WSGI threads on shutdown.

DO NOT MERGE THIS PATCH

Change-Id: I713b0f69185ce5c4cee9c01ccd795de88cac919a
Depends-On: Ie02ec5328797a20563d7b930c74e521a40cf38d7

commit_message:
Use min and max on IntOpt option types

Latest version of oslo.config support the ability to set valid
range on IntOpt option values.  This path makes use of that feature
for a number of options with well known minimum and maximum values.

Change-Id: Ie4b081bdaa373c9dedf7dd0c9884553ffb42b61c

commit_message:
Adjust haproxy rise

Change haproxy settings rise to 30. Keystone will be considered as
operational after 30 successful checks by a 2 seconds intervals.
It requires only 2*30 seconds to make it operational after the
haproxy backend was marked as down/nosrv.
Adjust Keystone memcached dead_retry setting to 60s to match
the changed rise value.

Change-Id: I0d6ff85376c78c0c4f1627fe9628c9ab3c686795
Closes-Bug: 1480153
Co-Authored-By: Sergii Golovatiuk <sgolovatiuk@mirantis.com>
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Change request header in HaProxy configuration for Heat API

Set requests header for Heat API service in HaProxy configuration to
'https' if ssl is used. It will help to avoid the problem with
wrong redirect during getting some info from Heat.

Change-Id: Ia2ce1d9965d571768f8ec26763b3d3afe4e19bdd
Closes-bug: #1486611

commit_message:
Validate service_identity resources

* When creating an user, show a warning if no password has been set.
* When creating a service, validate that a service_type is set.
* When creating endpoints, validate *_url are set.

It avoid catalog failures if a parameter is missing.

Change-Id: Ibe6c467a875bbdb09faad91d7ee39edf35e30624

To restrict oslo_db version from automatic update

this patch restricts that to <=2.3 so things won't
break.

[{'number': 4, 'created': '2015-08-18 04:02:58.000000000', 'files': ['playbooks/roles/ceph_client/tasks/ceph_config.yml'], 'message': 'Use slurp to get the content of the ceph.conf file

Using slurp will copy the original file entirely, the command strips

commit_message:
Use slurp to get the content of the ceph.conf file

Using slurp will copy the original file entirely, the command strips
new lines at the end of the file and ceph complain when \n on the last
line is missing.

Implements: blueprint ceph-block-devices

Change-Id: I321071fad9af332243a86f5840399e3363dfb37a

commit_message:
vmware: update help text for vmware.cluster_name option

Commit dcd33757dbcfee3c9a0e623f04a722c91de7ed0c added a check and
warning if multiple cluster names are specified since we want to map one
nova-compute service to a single vmware cluster.

This adds the same information to the config option help text since
that's what goes in the docs and the nova.conf.sample file for operators
to read before using the option (since they might not see the warning in
the logs).

The plan is to eventually enforce this with change
Ifc17c5049e3ed29c8dd130339207907b00433960.

The 12.0.0 Liberty version reference is based on the version proposed
in change I6a35fa0dda798fad93b804d00a46af80f08d475c.

DocImpact: Updated help text for the vmware.cluster_name option. The
           Kilo release notes have been retroactively updated to state
           the deprecation warning since the original change did not
           have an UpgradeImpact tag in the commit mesage.

Change-Id: Iff3d9e70030058af319427dd088efcb0fe2b979d

commit_message:
Ensure that nova and neutron provide consistent DHCP domain values

This patch adds the dhcp_domain config entry to nova.conf and
implements group_vars to default both nova and neutron's dhcp
domain values to be the same.

The individual values can still be overridden in user_variables
by using nova_dhcp_domain or neutron_dhcp_domain, but it's expected
that deployers would like these to be consistent.

Change-Id: I97beb78f62aeca2665ff72805056d36ead2adaaa
Closes-Bug: #1482045

commit_message:
Add dh-python pinning to get it from upstream

The problem is that for some reason dh-python
package is put in MOS repo. When we create
partial ubuntu mirror we do not put dh-python
package into the partial mirror. But then
when we use this partial mirror together with
debootstrap (which does not support multiple mirrors)
the base operating system can not be installed
because python3 package requires dh-python.

Besides, those packages which are listed explicitly
in fuel_agent/drivers/nailgun.py#L602-L644 should
be also explicitly mentioned in requirements-deb.txt.

Change-Id: I370a37dbe056d426b4f043893e279e4c869bdf11
Closes-Bug: #1484434

commit_message:
Fix missing OCF logging

W/o this patch, the most of the OCF agents
sending their own logs to nothere.

This is a major issue, because we want to
be able troubleshoot and keep OCF events
in syslog and collected at remote logs
server(s) as well.

The solution is to enable HA_LOGTAG and
HA_LOGFACILITY for each OCF script shipped
with the Fuel.

DocImpact: Ops guide. Logging events from
Fuel OCF agents will be collected both
locally in the /var/log/daemon.log and remotely,
with the file names based on the agent "foo-agent"
name as the "ocf-foo-agent.log". Note, that the
RabbitMQ will continue to log its OCF events
to the lrmd.log due to backwards compatibility reasons.

Closes-bug: #1487083
Change-Id: Ida2d5fe31de42d31131e0f3a3e7b1a771caf8dfd
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Hardware utils must get 'vendor' from sysfs

fuel-agent should use the same source for 'vendor' of block device
as fuel-nailgun-agent uses.

Otherwise, we could end up with situation when block device is being
filtered out during provisioning due to 'vendor' mismatch.
In that case, provisiong will fail.

Change-Id: If503e13e259bb123d95312ee37ce661905ea185f
Closes-Bug: #1487133

commit_message:
Nova: make nova server scenarios easier with existing users

nova.utils._boot_server() requires configuration for the "users"
context, but if running with existing users that will not
(necessarily) exist. This makes it handle existing users as well.

This change also switches the Nova _boot_server tests to ddt.

Change-Id: If9ca77fd73e881a0082757035cb67ffbc0914315

commit_message:
Configure the 'max_json_body_size' option for Heat

Default max template size and default max JSON body size
are 524288 (0.5 MB) and 1048576 (1 MB) respectively.
The value for max template size was increased to 5440000,
so we need to set appropriate value for max JSON body size
to 10880000.

Change-Id: Ib517117681bf70667e16b98d0eb34ac277d3ed31
Closes-bug: #1486616

commit_message:
Revert "Use generic keystone uri in devstack ..."

The keystone uri need to be without version for ceilometerclient,
but with the version with the v2 keystonecient.

This reverts commit a36b8ea4d9501ccb5af828b263e13f2f67ba5bcd.

And instead we strip the version from the keystone uri for
ceilometerclient.

commit_message:
Handle MessageTimeout to MigrationPreCheckError

There are a few checks before live-migration, if any of the
check failed, the live-migration can't be done. However
during _call_livem_checks_on_host check, because it's a
RPC call ,so it might result in a MessageTimeout exception.
If this occurs, we should safely revert its state,
since no real opperation occured.

This patch translates the MessageTimeout to
MigrationPreCheckError and leverage existing MigrationPreCheckError
processing to revert instance to normal state instead of error

Closes-Bug: 1435633

Change-Id: I8b484abb6650e14e2d225ca5e476d1fa7a6ee990

commit_message:
Allow a log dir that isn't the "service_name"

Galera logs by default to /var/log/mysql_logs these logs are being
ignored and not mounted properly on the host server, because the
service_name that is used to mount the log directory is "galera" and not
"mysql_logs".

This patch adds an option to set the log_directory specifically inside
the env.d yml files, but defaults to "service_name" when the
log_directory option isn't set. This will mean functionality remains
unchanged for all services.

Additionally, the log_directory has changed to "mysql_logs" for galera
containers, to resolve the galera log issue.

Change-Id: I18400248da455156dbba31b9c2ff254b58c51673
Closes-Bug: #1486955

commit_message:
Add new pci_max_virtual_functions config option

Adding new config option to allow the maximum number of virtual
functions per PCI device to be configured. This limit (MAX_FUNC)
is currently hardcoded to 7, which is less than what many newer
NICs are able to support.

Change-Id: Idff176d33583b8054dfd0c6334c002656f422914
Closes-Bug: #1471997

commit_message:
Run the post nodepool deploy checks from nodepool

Move the checks out of the nodepool dsvm job into nodepool itself so
that we can update the checks as we make changes to nodepool. This
simplifies making the tests more robust over time as we won't have to
update project-config too and it will be self testing.

Depends-on: Ie50c07b0581162c6fa297c0e1a5e38b4d1a7ca40
Change-Id: I66f22e73676000dc6fafc84baa816475aca1a32a

commit_message:
Fix _ensure_default_security_group logic

In a case when first attempt to fetch default security group
fails and attempt to add it fails too due to a concurrent insertion,
later attempt to fetch the same default sg may fail due to
REPEATABLE READ transaction isolation level.
For this case RetryRequest should be issued to restart the
whole transaction and be able to see default group.

The patch also removes 'while True' logic as it's unsafe

Closes-Bug: #1475938
Change-Id: I20f65d3eae9421429aced1f4586cb6988ab577ff

commit_message:
Restart haproxy in ns properly

Fix the regression introduced by
I720aff6ff0515b2b0ceb4b6ce821e2eaff70688a as it tried to kill by
processgroup without identifying it. PID != PGRP

Additionally, ps -o pgid= <PID> may return a leading space which breaks
the logic. This change removes the spaces from the ps results to ensure
we can properly use the pgid. This change also updates the restart logic
to not attempt to call the script within the namespace as that should be
properly handled by the ocf script.

Closes-Bug: 1487175
Closes-Bug: 1487056

Change-Id: I9030553ecbe6af05076e473f7d3a376fc8f5f660
Signed-off-by: Sergii Golovatiuk <sgolovatiuk@mirantis.com>
Co-Authored-By: Alex Schultz <aschultz@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Initial msync run for all Puppet OpenStack modules

This patch is the initial modulesync run, it impacts:

* gitignore: just a sync between projects
* gemfile:
  - update and allow to setup facter version and gem source
  - split beaker gems with a dedicated group
  - switch to rspec-puppet 2.2.0
* rakefile:
  - use the new syntax for lint configuration
  - add a acceptance target
* acceptance:
  - sync nodesets
* spec: added rspec coverage report

Change-Id: Ie9df0e87edc2a64e1b583cf2e0d681799b5531cf

reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 8736, 'name': 'Terry Howe', 'email': 'terrylhowe@gmail.com', 'username': 'terrylhowe'}]

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-08-19 18:50:05.000000000', 'files': ['openstack/compute/v2/extension.py', 'openstack/network/v2/extension.py', 'openstack/tests/unit/network/v2/test_extension.py', 'openstack/tests/unit/compute/v2/test_extension.py'], 'message': "Fix find_extension for Network and Compute proxies

The Extension resource for both Network and Compute were missing two
pieces that would help their find_extension methods work: for one, the
`alias` is actually the ID of an extension, and no ID value was set. If
we knew what the ID was, we could find it (or not find it) directly.
Before that can even be done, we would need to be able to get it by ID,

Change-Id: Id2a2071e9649edca78b2a5455a27e45443d6e8c9
"}]
commit_message:
Fix find_extension for Network and Compute proxies

The Extension resource for both Network and Compute were missing two
pieces that would help their find_extension methods work: for one, the
`alias` is actually the ID of an extension, and no ID value was set. If
we knew what the ID was, we could find it (or not find it) directly.
Before that can even be done, we would need to be able to get it by ID,
and we didn't have allow_retrieve set on either of those resources.
Allowing Extension resources to be retrieved by ID causes them to now be
found.

Closes-Bug: 1456317

commit_message:
Initial msync run for all Puppet OpenStack modules

This patch is the initial modulesync run, it impacts:

* gitignore: just a sync between projects
* gemfile:
  - update and allow to setup facter version and gem source
  - split beaker gems with a dedicated group
  - switch to rspec-puppet 2.2.0
* rakefile:
  - use the new syntax for lint configuration
  - add a acceptance target
* acceptance:
  - sync nodesets
* spec: added rspec coverage report

Change-Id: Ie10f1467374a9c254515172f5ddc53f2e628c602

z/VM is a hypervisor running on IBM System Z. This patch
adds the definitions needed for binding ports and defining
the ZVM agent identifier.

The mechanism driver is part of a separate networking-zvm repository,
but we still need those definitions in neutron to ensure that
they will stay unique and do not get changed.

'}]
commit_message:
Add z/VM mechanism driver definitions to support IBM z/VM agent

z/VM is a hypervisor running on IBM System Z. This patch
adds the definitions needed for binding ports and defining
the ZVM agent identifier.

The mechanism driver is part of a separate networking-zvm repository,
but we still need those definitions in neutron to ensure that
they will stay unique and do not get changed.

This is just adding the definitions.

Closes-Bug: #1476752

Change-Id: I38365e841438438c1f508782d8a44fc8659f25a7

commit_message:
Moving .rst format files to main admin-guide-cloud folder

This change moves the .rst files into the main adming-guide-cloud
folder now conversion is complete. changes to the project config
and to the openstack manuals to stop sync of .xml files
are also needed.

Change-Id: I498e8d6ac3cb80da413e23b14a0959abd58e7d79
Implements: blueprint reorganise-user-guides

commit_message:
Adapt SnapshotController to view builder

Snapshots were not using the view builder to translate responses, unlike
other resources like volumes and backups.

This patch moves snapshots to use the view builder like the rest.

Change-Id: Iec6873aedcf126f00c81fd016acfc8db9a5e512c

commit_message:
Pay attention to disabled quotas which are defined in a config file

Since Nova doesn't currently provide an API call to indicate whether
its quotas are disabled, we could use a parameter named
'enable_quotas' within 'OPENSTACK_HYPERVISOR_FEATURES' setting for
this purpose. This allows to avoid errors while trying to update
quotas which are disabled on service side. Also make disabled_quotas
collection to be a set instead of a list - this removes duplicate
fields that appear due to some possible quota overlaps between Nova
and Neutron.

DocImpact

Change-Id: I10923f147e4c323aba8bbcc130d2016ad6725e86
Closes-Bug: #1286099

Change-Id: I12207f3bd0b0a30e0d03fd87ec37cd82fe454c86

commit_message:
AVAILABLE_REGIONS picker should be responsive

The region selector located on the right side of the topbar should
be responsive, and should be collected into the responsive menu.

Also, it should be an anchor rather than a button, so that it shares
all the same stylings :)

Change-Id: Id663dded6f4420575d38449751548cd03b3911a6
Closes-bug: #1485925

commit_message:
Fix init-scripts element path munging and deps

There is a bug where the init scripts element incorrectly munges the
install path making it useless. Also removing the dep on rsync since
this occurs from inside the chroot.

commit_message:
l2pop: check port mac in pre-commit to stop change

Check that a port mac address hasn't changed during the precommit
phase of the port update rather than the post commit so the resulting
exception actually stops it from happening.

Change-Id: I62f120b3c954fa4251a7d676cf2c623e6da5a98b
Closes-Bug: #1486379

commit_message:
Fix stack-list after failed update

When a update is being performed, the existing template is updated
incrementally as resources change. Now if update fails, template will
have mix of resources from existing and new template. Hence we need to
ensure we have the user params of both.

Change-Id: I9e6831c58b167809e3faed519d2fb4f7c61244fc
Closes-Bug: #1477812

commit_message:
Improve logging for agent driver

* Added debug logging for every command and for lookup call. Redundant logging
  dropped from prepare_image.
* Log more steps as INFO (currently it looks like power on, power on, done):
  1. When ramdisk is booted and ready
  2. When image writing is done
* Several small improvements

Change-Id: I70d473e446e047140a02e19f21217b48de5f74a8

commit_message:
Change and edit of Ironic Installation Guide

Follow the Documentation conventions:
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Documentation/Conventions
* Change service names
* Titles should not be capitalized - only first word
* Do not use non English word "e.g.", use "for example"
* Do not use backend, use back end for the noun
  & back-end for the adjective
* Change ironic node to bare metal node
* Add spaces where necessary, and remove where unnecessary

Co-Authored-By: KATO Tomoyuki <kato.tomoyuki@jp.fujitsu.com>
Change-Id: Icb897ad3ba1d182d0778e3db2222d68c35689258

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-08-20 09:16:58.000000000', 'files': ['deployment/puppet/openstack/manifests/compute.pp', 'tests/noop/spec/hosts/roles/compute_spec.rb'], 'message': 'nova: make block migration consistent with live one

Block migration flags default to tunneled migration (via libvirt
connection), while for live migration we explicitly avoid that in
favor of plain migration (direct connection between qemu instances).

Make the behaviour of both types of migrations consistent by removing
the VIR_MIGRATE_TUNNELLED flag from the block migration flags.

This effectively fixes the issue with the libvirt version we have,
which segfaults in tunneled migration.

Another reason to give up on tunneled migration is LP #1246201, fix
for which will be only available for plain migration.

Closes-Bug: #1486070

Change-Id: I855ada6d6583c7d5ca2bae9e52bc952ccffe76fb
'}]
commit_message:
nova: make block migration consistent with live one

Block migration flags default to tunneled migration (via libvirt
connection), while for live migration we explicitly avoid that in
favor of plain migration (direct connection between qemu instances).

Make the behaviour of both types of migrations consistent by removing
the VIR_MIGRATE_TUNNELLED flag from the block migration flags.

This effectively fixes the issue with the libvirt version we have,
which segfaults in tunneled migration.

Another reason to give up on tunneled migration is LP #1246201, fix
for which will be only available for plain migration.

Closes-Bug: #1486070

Change-Id: I855ada6d6583c7d5ca2bae9e52bc952ccffe76fb

commit_message:
Make driver properties discoverable in REST API

Drivers expose their required properties via the REST endpoint
"/v1/drivers/XXXX/properties". But the same is not discoverable
via API. This patch is make driver properties discoverable via API.

Change-Id: I58886030ab77467f270ad2ef963e5f695bfe21b5
Closes-Bug: #1475744

commit_message:
Add support for additional nova.conf options

The following options have been added to improve support for rbd (Ceph)
in nova.

libvirt/hw_disk_discard = unmap
www.sebastien-han.fr/blog/2015/02/02/openstack-and-ceph-rbd-discard

libvirt/disk_cachemodes = "network=writeback"
www.sebastien-han.fr/blog/2013/08/22/configure-rbd-caching-on-nova

http://ceph.com/docs/master/rbd/rbd-openstack/

DocImpact
Implements: blueprint ceph-block-devices
Change-Id: Ibf717fa88326805254ca31421d9a77c47b326b67

revisions:
[{'number': 7, 'created': '2015-08-20 06:34:41.000000000', 'files': ['neutronclient/tests/unit/test_cli20.py'], 'message': 'Adding registration interface for non_admin_status_resources

By default, admin_state_up is set to True in _test_create_resource.
If a resource doesn't need to package admin_state_up then it's resource
name should be mentioned in "non_admin_status_resources" explicitly.

The current logic doesn't work for the extension project/s which are
developed outside the tree but depends upon the existing test framework
for running their unit test-cases. To address this issue, the patch adds
a new registration interface for non_admin_status_resources using which
one can add their resource to non_admin_status_resources and avoid
admin_state_up packaging.

Change-Id: I2abf3bd038f7e444818bfebfed37713ba536f1b5
'}]
commit_message:
Adding registration interface for non_admin_status_resources

By default, admin_state_up is set to True in _test_create_resource.
If a resource doesn't need to package admin_state_up then it's resource
name should be mentioned in "non_admin_status_resources" explicitly.

The current logic doesn't work for the extension project/s which are
developed outside the tree but depends upon the existing test framework
for running their unit test-cases. To address this issue, the patch adds
a new registration interface for non_admin_status_resources using which
one can add their resource to non_admin_status_resources and avoid
admin_state_up packaging.

Change-Id: I2abf3bd038f7e444818bfebfed37713ba536f1b5

commit_message:
Revert "Make nova-network use conductor for security groups refresh"

This change reverts commit b1838c258df2465756e551fdb879b1d4a748cb2b.

This makes network manager go back to issuing security group refresh
calls directly instead of going through conductor now that the
compute api call it is making is converted to objects.

This also removes and deprecates the conductor proxying code that
becomes unused after this change.

Related to blueprint liberty-objects

Change-Id: I74e002384b11063e30450e3854a95b6b848ddfb6

commit_message:
Use graceful OVS restart by default

drop_flows_on_start option is intended to manage graceful OVS agent restart.
It should be set to False to enable this feature.
Also changed the default value according to the upstream patch.

Upstream patch: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/211986/
Change-Id: I5c09a00f2df43745eaf2c9949ca831cc099d1995
Closes-bug: #1483253

commit_message:
Handle libvirt/cpu_model option

CPU model name shouldn't be set when a host CPU mode is requested.
The CPU model is incompatible with CPU mode unless cpu_mode set
to "custom" value.

Upstream-CR:#214542

Closes-Bug:#1486517

Change-Id: Ia2b332ca1fae6ae912a7e95f43266a445300a799

commit_message:
Set iptables-persistent install execution to append to log

This patch sets the command to install the iptables-persistent
package in the run-playbooks script to append its output to the
existing log instead of overwriting it.

This is to ensure that outputs from both commands are captured,
not just the second one.

Change-Id: I4d45382cb44c5f811818fe1229a63e6a2c2ecdee
Partial-Bug: #1485917

commit_message:
Fix "tox -egenconfig" by avoiding the MODULEPATH env variable

MODULEPATH is apparently a well known variable from environment-modules
package and was causing the sample configuration generation to fail.

Closes-Bug: #1437904

commit_message:
Check RabbitMQ cluster status via REST API during cluster create

This is replacing the TaskFlow task to check when a rabbit node begins to
respond to port 5672.  We now use rabbits management plugin and REST API
to check when the cluster is active and able to consume jobs. The new task
is added at the end of the create_cluster flow.  This is (arbitrarily) going
to the 0th node's RabbitMQ Management port.

Change-Id: I9dffdefd9cdcd6317f5c3114c59b4b30b8218239

Sphinx and OpenStack documentation standards require the use of
RST formatted documentation.  In order to get out docs integrated
into docs.openstack.org, the following steps must be taken:
1. we need to first convert the documentation to RST
2. sPhinx support must be added to the repository
3. project-config must be updated with a publish-docs job

The ability to pubish to docs.openstack.org is a privilege only
available to Big Tent projects.  As a result, we should be taking
advantage of this to help spread the word on our implementation.

Note the documentation was converted with a tool called pandoc
the syntax of which was:

git mv $FILE.md $FILE.rst
pandoc -f markdown -t rst file.md > z
mv z $FILE.rst

Change-Id: Id2be5dfbc0c8dc02a77716f09ff3c7a9b0a18543
'}]
commit_message:
Convert MD to RST to publish to docs.openstack.org

Sphinx and OpenStack documentation standards require the use of
RST formatted documentation.  In order to get out docs integrated
into docs.openstack.org, the following steps must be taken:
1. we need to first convert the documentation to RST
2. sPhinx support must be added to the repository
3. project-config must be updated with a publish-docs job

The ability to pubish to docs.openstack.org is a privilege only
available to Big Tent projects.  As a result, we should be taking
advantage of this to help spread the word on our implementation.

Note the documentation was converted with a tool called pandoc
the syntax of which was:

git mv $FILE.md $FILE.rst
pandoc -f markdown -t rst file.md > z
mv z $FILE.rst

Change-Id: Id2be5dfbc0c8dc02a77716f09ff3c7a9b0a18543

commit_message:
Activate pep8 check that _ is imported

Remove the specification in tox.ini that _ is a builtin so that
it will no longer assume that _ does not need to be imported.
This helps ensure that the _ from i18n is used.

Activating this check did not flag any violations.

Change-Id: I3859d14cdc68e8559679e2707af0fe4254f8550c

commit_message:
Set cluster status to warning after deletion failed

Currently, cluster status will be set to ACTIVE after cluster
deletion failed for certain reason. This status may not be
appropriate since some nodes could have become unfunctional after
this deletion. So this patch sets cluster's status to WARNING after
cluster deletion failed for error or timeout to illustrated that
the cluster may have become unhealthy.

Change-Id: I1439e284ca0194b23cc2ba5b49e078468a2f84f0

commit_message:
Remove unnecessary ValueError exception

Agent object save method doesn't raise ValueError hence removed
unnecessary ValueError exception block while calling Agent object
save method.

ApiImpact: 400 BadRequest response will be returned in case invalid
agent id is provided during agent-delete, earlier it was returning
500 InternalServerError response.

Closes-Bug: 1463696
Change-Id: I600e70aff2d271e22ccad3b0302fc45a942c98bb

commit_message:
No longer deal with locales when generating Zanata

Zanata 3.7.1 moved locale configuration from the client having to
specify them in the zanata.xml file, to having the server make all
the decisions. As such, the server no longer includes any locales
information in the returned configuration.

Change-Id: I2e8870280c30a4b2983996e5e9803933db986add

During the upgrade of the API surface with running computes we're
going to see disconnects and reconnects for the service group API (as
conductor is gone). This is not an ERROR, but a normally expected
thing.

Change the connect to an INFO

Change the disconnect to a WARNING (if it happens a lot someone should
look into it).

In both cases try to be a lot more specific, because 'model server' is
really vague and not a term we use in ops facing documentation.

Change-Id: I55417a5b91282c69432bb2ab64441c5cea474d31
"}]
commit_message:
don't report service group connection events as errors in dbdriver

During the upgrade of the API surface with running computes we're
going to see disconnects and reconnects for the service group API (as
conductor is gone). This is not an ERROR, but a normally expected
thing.

Change the connect to an INFO

Change the disconnect to a WARNING (if it happens a lot someone should
look into it).

In both cases try to be a lot more specific, because 'model server' is
really vague and not a term we use in ops facing documentation.

Change-Id: I55417a5b91282c69432bb2ab64441c5cea474d31

commit_message:
Add 'reverse_lazy' for 'success_url' in admin volume type panel

In the admin volume type panel, several 'success_url' in views miss
'reverse_lazy', this result in the cancel action redirect to wrong url.
For example, when right click the "Create Volume Type" button and open
a new page, click the cancel button will cast error.

Closes-Bug: #1487271
Change-Id: Ia1a16d34c5636294f5a1fda8e061f47c2b9a5d65

commit_message:
libvirtd: Bug fix for deleting snapshot of attached volume

	When using gluster as cinder backing storage,
	deleting a snapshot of an attached volume will cause
	Nova to reference _get_snap_dev, which will have
	a backing_store of None. This patch adds a simple check
	of backing_store to prevent this error.

	Close-Bug: #1477110

Change-Id: I08c1a0adbbf8c872795fc71bd4c13673ec7544de

commit_message:
Notify specific host in DVR create/update port

Notify L3 agent when create or update port in _dvrscheduler_db.py.
Why use notify all L3 agent rather than specific L3 agent?

In pulic clouds, there are many machines. If fanout the RPC messages
when create/update ports, it will make MQ more heavier and plugins
and agents can't synchronous when MQ blocked. So I suggest use notify
specific host rather than fanout.

Close-bug: #1486795
Change-Id: I1330d933bef6a2d3671b639d305e8395cf039021

commit_message:
Enhance tests for saml2 signing exception logging

There was no test that verified that the log message was generated
correctly when there was an exception from the xmlsec1 binary. The
test shows that the log message isn't generated correctly but
instead causes a TypeError to be raised.

The test__sign_assertion_fileutils_exc test is also enhanced to
verify that the error is logged correctly.

Change-Id: I5b7c22d27bad241339fdacae8b61973d45d55d30
Partial-Bug: 1484735

commit_message:
Prevent deletion of a subnet with lbaas v1 pool

When using LBaaS and trying to delete a subnet, neutron has no way of
knowing if the subnet is associated to some pool. As a result, the
subnet is deleted but the pool remains associated to the (now
nonexistent) subnet_id.  This patch adds a check in LBaaS side to
prevent such a case, using the callbacks system.

Closes-Bug: #1413817
Change-Id: I1a8893453b0b623df792fdabcf540163007a3f33
Depends-on: I3d5e231b67c72ffd919c92d65b57da56c63e053c

commit_message:
resource failure causes nested stacks to be rolled back

an update_cancel RPC call for a nested stacks whenever an update
operation was cancelled in the parent stack.Unfortunately this always
triggers a rollback.
In this change, resource failure with nested stacks will cancel any
in-progress update but not roll back by default (roll back only when
rollblack cancel exception raised).
The Operator can retry in this way without waiting for timeout
or overall roll back occurred.
Change-Id: I94d75a21367f39c17a9b40b5d23405a28873cd1a
Closes-Bug: #1475057

commit_message:
Remove the --autofree option from boot.ipxe

Many distros create and distribute images based on the v1.0.0 code from
iPXE (stable release). This version does not support the --autofree flag
that we use in our boot.ipxe template.

While using --autofree may be a good practice (it frees the image after
chainloading) it's not mandatory and by removing it we will get a much
support for people using the stable version of iPXE and it will continue
to work with the images built from the master.

Closes-Bug: #1486950
Change-Id: Iff936b72aa897c02bd8210cb7687abd255f47e53

commit_message:
The API unit tests for serial console use http instead of ws

The serial console will only work if a websocket URL is returned,
e.g. "ws://127.0.0.1:6083/" [1]
The API unit tests use "http" as scheme name, which could lead to
misinterpretation of the capabilities of this feature.They should
use "ws" in the tests to avoid misleading.

[1] table 3.53;

nova.utils._get_root_helper() should be public

The nova.utils._get_root_helper() method is used outside of the
nova.utils module, so we should make it public.
Change the method to nova.utils.get_root_helper()

commit_message:
Remove docker-compose

This patch removes docker-compose and merges the documentation
This change also merges the documentation for Ansible into the dev-quickstart
and removes all references in the documentation to using compose.
This change removes kolla-compose and genenv.
This change slightly modifies init-runonce to work without compose.

Change-Id: Ida0bcc78f4822fcf45819864964bae4715ff919e
Partially-Implements: bluerpint remove-internal-config

We need to be able to use keystone /v3 API for Neutron
handshake. This means allowing operators to specify a

commit_message:
Support keystone /v3 API url in [neutron]admin_auth_url

We need to be able to use keystone /v3 API for Neutron
handshake. This means allowing operators to specify a
admin domain name/id (and use 'default' as domain name if
there is no entry in nova.conf). We use the generic
Password class in keystone client to switch between /v2
and /v3 based on the url.

Change-Id: I135a240515d42de75b3d0def70be2c08dd5bfded

commit_message:
Setup firewall filters only for required ports

We can skip trying to setup firewall filters for ports which are
having port_security_enabled as False or which are not associated
to any security group.

Closes-Bug: #1482554

Change-Id: Ie65201308d93c746fe4ef38f402ec300227b7d27

commit_message:
Add missing @require_context

@require_context wrapper is required to make sure the
functions must have the first param as RequestContext
to prevent misuage, the wrapper should be applied to
db functions otherwise we will send wrong info to
db layer function, add the wrapper would report
error eailer.

key_pair_count_by_user is similar to db other functions,
so it should have same decorateors the others have.
Because there is already a test for this wrapper.

Change-Id: I98efbf8347b0cf7bf21077c4654c47b666fe8dd9

commit_message:
Switch locale marker to locale_with_underscore

Zanata 3.7.1 has moved much of the locale logic to the server, which
means we can no longer make use of client side transforms, such as
map-from, so set the locale to locale_with_underscore so dashes are
replaced with underscores.

Change-Id: I0bde5b84388f2be39c85600870ec530e8b5c07a5

commit_message:
test_plug_vip not testing properly in py34

Not sure if this is actually the fix, but by passing a pure NotFound as
a side-effect, the building of that exception actually fails, which
causes the test to fail (as expected) but not for the reason expected...
NotFound expects at LEAST code=<response_code> and optionally a message.

Change-Id: I0a8539da164074249aa93b70d2cf5af72d1036b4

commit_message:
Add a fullstack fake VM, basic connectivity test

* Full stack tests' fake VMs are represented via a namespace,
  MAC, IP address and default gateway. They're plugged to an OVS
  bridge via an OVS internal port. As opposed to the current
  fake machine class used in functional testing, this new fake
  machine also creates a Neutron port via the API and sets the
  IP and MAC according to it. It also sets additional attributes
  on the OVS port to allow the OVS agent to do its magic.
* The functional fake machine and the full stack fake machine
  should continue to share commonalities.
* The fullstack fake machine currently takes the IP address
  from the port and statically assigns it to the namespace
  device. Later when I'll add support for the DHCP agent
  in full stack testing this assignment will look for the dhcp
  attribute of the subnet and either assign the IP address
  via 'ip' or call a dhcp client.
* Added a basic L2 connectivity test between two such machines
  on the same Neutron network.
* OVSPortFixture now uses OVSInterfaceDriver to plug the port
  instead of replicate a lot of the code. I had to make a
  small change to _setup_arp_spoof_for_port since all OVS ports
  are now created with their external-ids set.

Change-Id: Ib985b7e742f58f1a6eb6fc598df3cbac31046951

The code was checking the tenant to determine if octavia had created the
vip port or not. If it did create the vip port then it would delete it, if not

commit_message:
Check for port ownership on vip deallocation

The code was checking the tenant to determine if octavia had created the
vip port or not. If it did create the vip port then it would delete it, if not
it would not delete the port. Since neutron-lbaas merged a change that set
the device_owner appropriately on the port, we can now check device_owner for
ownership. This also adds octavia as the device_owner of the vip port if
it does create it and sets the device_id to the load balancer's id.

Change-Id: I12adf2824c77f633be7499f120e6f5b3a9c326ef

commit_message:
Python 3: encode or decode i/o data of Popen.communicate()

In Python 3, input and output for Popen.communicate() is bytes type.
Therefore, encode input data and decode return data for Popen.communicate().

Change-Id: I70f009e3366f0eeda5790652ea14f3627b934664
Blueprint: neutron-python3
Closes-Bug: #1479159

commit_message:
Fix race conditions in config overrides tasks

    * Convert configuration casts into blocking calls and move them
      from the task manager to the API. Update the Trove records
      only after a successful update on the guestagent.

    * Change the way how we apply the configuration changes.

       - On attach: Apply the values dynamically only if all of them
                    can be applied at once. Put the instance into
                    the 'RESTART_REQUIRED' state otherwise.
       - On detach: Apply the values dynamically only if:
                    a) Default values for all of them are
                       available in the configuration template.
                    b) All values can be applied at once.
                   Put the instance into the 'RESTART_REQUIRED'
                   state otherwise.

    * Remove override template resolution. Pass override values in a
      Python dict (like it is for 'apply_overrides').
      The user-provided configuration values do not get resolved and
      are applied as supplied by the user - hence no need for a template.
      It also avoids the need to double-parse the overrides in
      guestagents that do not support configuration imports.

    * Moved MySQL-specific value conversions (K, M, G suffixes)
      down to the MySQL guestagent.

    * Update the MySQL 'update_overrides' methods to accept both
      Python dicts and rendered strings. This is for backwards
      compatibility with older task managers that send overrides as
      a string.

    * Remove deprecated methods from the taskmanager.

Closes-Bug: 1468488
Change-Id: Ie125131945ad82afe6663e6c5a5d70c6e949c60b

commit_message:
Allow use of our test fixtures with alternate assignment models

For developers working on out-of-tree alternate assignment models
our current test fixtures error out if such an assignment model
does not support the existing APIs. To ease development of
such out-of-tree models, which typically would come with their
own replacement for the general assignment tests, our text fixtures
should at least allow these API to return NotImplemented - and if
so, to carry on without raising an error.

Change-Id: Iedbfee867435fbc8e941184ac963665c4b49bd82

commit_message:
Trim spaces off of pid to fix haproxy stop ocf

The stop command was not properly stopping haproxy due to a leading
space before the pid that was preventing the ocf script from properly
stopping the haproxy process. This change trims the spaces to fix the
errors being reported and allows the script to correctly stop the
haproxy process.

Change-Id: I8e5b98985db7ec2c398313e2437153f0666c4ccd
Closes-Bug: 1487056

commit_message:
Make compute_api.trigger_members_refresh() issue a single db call

This method currently make n db calls equal to the number of security
groups given by group_ids parameter plus n db calls equal to the
number of rules found for those security groups.

This change make use of a new db api method to replace the many calls
the current code issues to get the list of instances affected by changes
to some security groups.

This is also a precursor for making network manager call this directly
instead of going through conductor by making the db call go through a
new instance object method.

Related to blueprint liberty-objects

Change-Id: Ic7e1a0b7a8f79dfc53adda6b61f54dd1eff78f80

commit_message:
add poll history to avoid duplicate samples

this is a patch until we properly separate polling logic. this
patch adds history so if a resource is defined in separate pipelines
it will only be processed in one. by doing this, we send only a
single copy of each sample and it can be processed appropriately
by the notification agent

this removes duplication check as it is covered by poll history and
removes the pipeline references in polling.

Change-Id: I9c1d3e25740fff5281d796c7bfea2f0e105bb5c5
Closes-Bug: #1480442

reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 8736, 'name': 'Terry Howe', 'email': 'terrylhowe@gmail.com', 'username': 'terrylhowe'}]
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-08-20 17:55:03.000000000', 'files': ['openstack/object_store/v1/_proxy.py'], 'message': "Get container off of an Object if its passed

The previous object operations on object_store proxy were too strict on
requiring a container argument to be passed, and in some cases they were
too loose.

When an Object is passed, look to see if it has a container attribute
already set and use it if so. If that doesn't work out, look at the
container argument, which that that point would have to be specified. If
we get a container out of that, use it. After this, we won't be able to
do any object operations with a container, so raise ValueError
specifying that a container has to be provided.

Change-Id: I6b587831321998245815fccf8f822025e83141c5
Closes-Bug: 1487147
"}]
commit_message:
Get container off of an Object if its passed

The previous object operations on object_store proxy were too strict on
requiring a container argument to be passed, and in some cases they were
too loose.

When an Object is passed, look to see if it has a container attribute
already set and use it if so. If that doesn't work out, look at the
container argument, which that that point would have to be specified. If
we get a container out of that, use it. After this, we won't be able to
do any object operations with a container, so raise ValueError
specifying that a container has to be provided.

Change-Id: I6b587831321998245815fccf8f822025e83141c5
Closes-Bug: 1487147

commit_message:
Fixed event requeuing/ack on publisher failure

Event should be acked or requeued when either event
conversion or event publishing fails by configuring
ack_on_event_error in configuration.

When publishing fails, the exception is not raised
in the pipeline and event does not get acked or
requeued, with a Handled message sent to transport
leading to event loss.

This fix raises the exception in pipeline on publish
failure and improves unit tests to test event handling
with a real pipeline.

Change-Id: Ia00a9ce30c5b03269091caa7f5edca9fcf113aff
Closes-Bug: #1482797

commit_message:
Setup base neutron network driver

There are common methods that all neutron based network drivers will most
likely implement the same way.  To prevent duplicate code, a common base driver
for all neutron drivers has been created. In the process of splitting this out,
cleaning up of some existing code was done as well.

The network driver's plug_network and unplug_network methods took an
amphora_id as a parameter, but it was always assumed to be the compute_id.
This parameter has been changed to compute_id.

The octavia interface network model originally had just a single ip_address,
but to more accurately reflect what neutron and probably other networking
as a services will return, this has been changed to fixed_ips because
interfaces and ports can have multiple ip addresses.

Other cleanup includes calling the network drivers own get_network, get_subnet,
and get_port methods instead of calling the neutron client's show_network,
show_subnet, and show_port methods.  Also, all of these changes required some
test changes as well.

Change-Id: Ie6ebc5bc8babe8562c280ba12a1feab21b4ff3f9

commit_message:
Added new test for CORS Simple Headers

It turns out that the simple header list outlined by the CORS
specification includes additional headers that were missed
during the initial implementation. This patch adds those
headers, and includes a test to enforce it moving forward.

commit_message:
Restore backward compat of paste factory

Some application inherits from our middleware class

When we homogenize the signature and configuration handling
of all middlewares we break them.

This change fixes that.

Closes-bug: #1486735

Change-Id: I40c3d59110c6f8c5a1b3d3ccc734dc441069b025

commit_message:
Ensure vrouter pacemaker service runs

This change updates the cluster-vrouter task to ensure the p_vrouter
pacemaker service runs on all controllers. Without this change, the
clone_p_vrouter service only runs on the primary-controller and is not
run anywhere else if the primary-controller is lost.

Change-Id: I60cbb28ee39c1a877a622dfcb96ba588af15ae7d
Closes-Bug: 1486641

commit_message:
Revert "DVR: fix router scheduling"

This change set introduces another problem where the snat namespace is not created when a gateway is set to the router after an interface is added to the router.

When a gateway is set after the interface is added to the router, the _get_candidates always returns saying that the router has already been scheduled and so the snat scheduling is not done.

This reverts commit 236e408272bcb9b8e957524864e571b5afdc4623.

Change-Id: I0d5d1a13745c8b4d9e0d25b4859f2f57d3272a5f

specification template. It incorporates the following

commit_message:
Allow Docker to make better use of cache

Docker cache takes into account things like filesize, hash of file,
and even timestamp and access times when determining whether to use
the cache or not. This modifies the build script to adjust all the
timestamps to 0 epoch. Since we dont care about timestamps this allows
us to make far better use of the cache, including when downloading and
creating tarballs for source builds.

Change-Id: Id4287cf1fcaa2de63feaab9e6f4ebbd4defdb768
Partially-Implements: blueprint build-script

commit_message:
Use correct config key in alembic extension

While the value we're looking for is passed into the Extension as
'alembic_repo_path' it is actually stored in the alembic config as
'script_location'. This change fixes the call to the alembic config
and retrieves 'script_location' instead.

Change-Id: Ia328e8230d33dc063c0d377e04f15f1ccaa4d500
Closes-Bug: #1486655

subject: Properly pass on Container in path_args
reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 1112, 'name': 'Everett Toews', 'email': 'everett.toews@rackspace.com', 'username': 'everett-toews'}, {'_account_id': 8257, 'name': 'Brian Curtin', 'email': 'brian@python.org', 'username': 'briancurtin'}, {'_account_id': 8736, 'name': 'Terry Howe', 'email': 'terrylhowe@gmail.com', 'username': 'terrylhowe'}]
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-08-19 17:24:19.000000000', 'files': ['openstack/tests/unit/object_store/v1/test_proxy.py', 'openstack/object_store/v1/_proxy.py'], 'message': "Properly pass on Container in path_args

Once we moved object_store from its own form of proxy to using the
BaseProxy methods, we lost proper handling of the container during
object-related operations. We need to pass on container.name, not the
full container object, so when instances were passed in a URL would be
created with the repr of an actual Container, which clearly doesn't
work.

There's an additional safety check in create_object to make sure a
container is passed in before trying an operation that won't work and
then raise a confusing exception.

Partial-Bug: 1485054

Change-Id: I85bb6f3b09a9617395dba0fd9becb62a8c4d7e68
"}]
commit_message:
Properly pass on Container in path_args

Once we moved object_store from its own form of proxy to using the
BaseProxy methods, we lost proper handling of the container during
object-related operations. We need to pass on container.name, not the
full container object, so when instances were passed in a URL would be
created with the repr of an actual Container, which clearly doesn't
work.

There's an additional safety check in create_object to make sure a
container is passed in before trying an operation that won't work and
then raise a confusing exception.

Partial-Bug: 1485054

Change-Id: I85bb6f3b09a9617395dba0fd9becb62a8c4d7e68

commit_message:
V2: Do not validate image schema when listing

Previously when listing images via v2, the first image of each batch
was validated against the v2 schema.

This could lead to unpredictable behaviour where a particular image
which failed the schema check may or may not be the first of a batch.

In some cases it also meant that operation by one user could affect the
ability of another other to list images.

Change-Id: I22974a3e3d9cbdd254099780752ae45ff2a557af
Closes-bug: 1477910

subject: Ensure threshold is always printed as a decimal
reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 2419, 'name': 'Roland Hochmuth', 'email': 'roland.hochmuth@hpe.com', 'username': 'roland-hochmuth-s'}, {'_account_id': 11182, 'name': 'Deklan Dieterly', 'username': 'ddieterly', 'inactive': True}, {'_account_id': 12512, 'name': 'Deklan Dieterly', 'email': 'deklan.dieterly@hpe.com', 'username': 'deklan'}]
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-08-15 04:57:28.000000000', 'files': ['java/monasca-common-model/src/test/java/monasca/common/model/alarm/AlarmSubExpressionTest.java', 'java/monasca-common-model/src/main/java/monasca/common/model/alarm/AlarmSubExpression.java'], 'message': "Ensure threshold is always printed as a decimal

If threshold is very large, for example, 21474836480, it would get
printed using scientific notation. If that expression was then used
to recreate the AlarmSubExpression, it would fail because the parser
didn't handle scientific notation.

So, instead use DecimalFormat to ensure a valid decimal number without
scientific notation. This then limits the threshold to 15 decimal
places, but that should be enough. It would be better to have no limit
but I have not been able to find a way to do that.

Change-Id: I0511bd73a0ab65498dd615d8f5049b5663720b6a
"}]
commit_message:
Ensure threshold is always printed as a decimal

If threshold is very large, for example, 21474836480, it would get
printed using scientific notation. If that expression was then used
to recreate the AlarmSubExpression, it would fail because the parser
didn't handle scientific notation.

So, instead use DecimalFormat to ensure a valid decimal number without
scientific notation. This then limits the threshold to 15 decimal
places, but that should be enough. It would be better to have no limit
but I have not been able to find a way to do that.

commit_message:
Disable cinder and cinder_backup testing in tempest

As hpcloud instances struggle to complete builds in master, we need
to disable cinder testing in tempest as it appears that something
has changed in cinder (Liberty) which is causing the issue.

This is a workaround to allow development to continue while the root
cause is figured out.

Change-Id: I41afa7f09ab526e64c28aa87517c90cc2bf336c5
Related-Bug: #1485917

we have multiple queries to build events in sql. we need consistent
reads across these queries but postgres defaults to READ COMMIT
isolation which doesn't guarantee consistency in transaction.

commit_message:
postgres isolation level produces inconsistent reads

we have multiple queries to build events in sql. we need consistent
reads across these queries but postgres defaults to READ COMMIT
isolation which doesn't guarantee consistency in transaction.
set isolation level to REPEATABLE READ just for get_events.
REPEATABLE READ is already default behaviour of mysql innodb

Change-Id: Ia1831e0df995c36e100b3c3c68897429e9784cd5
Closes-Bug: #1480490

         Refer bug 1402502 for details.

Solution: Update resource usage when suspend/resume is successful.
          And add a protection on resume action to avoid resource

Detail: 1, Modify nova.compute.manager.ComputeManager. At the end of
           Suspend/Resume, call _instance_update() to update resource
           usage.

        2, Modify nova.compute.resource_tracker.ResourceTracker. Use a
           dict to record the suspended instance. Skip suspended
           instances during resource statistic procedure.

        3, Modify nova.compute.api.API. Invoke new RPC resume_instance()
           inside nova.conductor.manager.ComputeTaskManager, which will

           for selecting destination. With both keywords, nova.scheduler
           will firstly select hosts/nodes included in suggested_nodes
           or suggested_hosts. Then nova.scheduler will check the host
           capactiy. If no host has capacity to start the vm, NoValidHost
           exception will be thrown.

commit_message:
Re-calculate resource usage for suspend/resume

Problem: The bug is the resource usage on database will not be updated
         after suspend/resume action. This will lead to the host
         resource cannot be reused after suspending instance(s)
         Refer bug 1402502 for details.

Solution: Update resource usage when suspend/resume is successful.
          And add a protection on resume action to avoid resource
          over-commitment on the host machine.

Detail: 1, Modify nova.compute.manager.ComputeManager. At the end of
           Suspend/Resume, call _instance_update() to update resource
           usage.

        2, Modify nova.compute.resource_tracker.ResourceTracker. Use a
           dict to record the suspended instance. Skip suspended
           instances during resource statistic procedure.

        3, Modify nova.compute.api.API. Invoke new RPC resume_instance()
           inside nova.conductor.manager.ComputeTaskManager, which will
           finally invoke RPC resume_instance() in
           nova.compute.manager.ComputeManager as previous.

        4, Add resume_instance() inside nova.conductor.ComputeTaskManager
           It will check original host capacity by invoking RPC call
           select_destinations() in nova.scheduler.host_manager.client

        5, New keywords 'suggested_nodes' and 'suggested_hosts' are added
           for selecting destination. With both keywords, nova.scheduler
           will firstly select hosts/nodes included in suggested_nodes
           or suggested_hosts. Then nova.scheduler will check the host
           capactiy. If no host has capacity to start the vm, NoValidHost
           exception will be thrown.

        6, Add unit test cases for modified code.

Closes-bug: 1402502

Change-Id: If51a9422f1c7e3c832b52a80ce706711f5718dde

commit_message:
Refactor the essential prop list of inspect driver

This patch is a groundwork for iRMC inspect driver [1], and refactors
the essential property list defined in iLO inspect driver into the common
base class.
This patch is also a reflection of the gerrit review comment [2] which
advised that the essential property list defined in iLO should be
removed in separate patch if you add the essential property list to
base.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/196480/
[2] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/196480/7/ironic/drivers/base.py

Change-Id: Iacce751bceb6ff8183245b359bb3117248f7322e

commit_message:
Fix create trove instance with a neutron port failed

Heat fails to create a trove instance with a neutron port, because it try to
get 'port' attribute from the instance properties, while the 'port' attribute
is in attribute 'networks' of instance properties.

Change-Id: I44b1f04398519cfc300cd8183148e8128d3d8fc8
Closes-Bug: #1484010

commit_message:
Fix bug sending sensor data for drivers w/o management

When a node's driver doesn't have management interface, it can't send
sensor data, so it spams to log: "Failed to get sensor data for...".

Such behavior confuses operator, so this change skip sending sensor
data if driver doesn't have management interface.

Change-Id: I9ce718166bbb39dbe3cdfee7613290d02adb312b
Closes-Bug: 1413618

commit_message:
Insert Cache-Control header into HTTP response

When the formatted entity from the controller level
contains the 'freshness' attribute, add it to the HTTP
response as the value of the 'max-age' attribute of the
Cache-Control header.

Partially-Implements: bp dynamic-policies-delivery

Change-Id: I5dbe51ccb5249579d6db8d35986a492eb8ab2214

[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-08-18 13:28:33.000000000', 'files': ['trove/guestagent/datastore/experimental/mongodb/service.py'], 'message': 'MongoDB create_admin_user not authorized

During cluster creation the taskmanager attempts to run
create_admin_user on the query router, but it fails as the connection is
not authorized if security/authorization is enabled. This causes the
cluster creation to fail.

The fix is to pass the localhost as the host for the client, then reset
it to the host address after.

Change-Id: I95083d0981231bfd19e9646446c25d0b3f112b12
Closes-bug: #1485232
'}]
commit_message:
MongoDB create_admin_user not authorized

During cluster creation the taskmanager attempts to run
create_admin_user on the query router, but it fails as the connection is
not authorized if security/authorization is enabled. This causes the
cluster creation to fail.

The fix is to pass the localhost as the host for the client, then reset
it to the host address after.

Change-Id: I95083d0981231bfd19e9646446c25d0b3f112b12
Closes-bug: #1485232

commit_message:
Fix cluster search logic

The SSP cluster code that searched for a specified cluster
name was expecting to get back a feed of entries when in fact
the search() method returns a list of Cluster wrappers.

Change-Id: I0d635a79d86951bc52757666de92db07da9e221c

commit_message:
Reflect provider change in puppet-openstacklib

With the creation of the new openstack_config provider, some processing
that was done in sahara_config has been centralized in
openstack_config.

Impacted methods are :

  * section
  * setting
  * separator

Also, this commit adds the fact that, when passing a specific string
(ensure_absent_val) the provider will behave as if ensure => absent was
specified. '<SERVICE DEFAULT>' is the default value for
ensure_absent_val.

The use case is the following :

sahara_config { 'DEFAULT/foo' : value => 'bar' } # will work as usual

sahara_config { 'DEFAULT/foo' : value => '<SERVICE DEFAULT>' } # will mean absent

That means that all the current :

if $myvar {
  sahara_config { 'DEFAULT/foo' : value => $myvar }
} else {
  sahara_config { 'DEFAULT/foo' : ensure => absent }
}

can be removed in favor of :

sahara_config { 'DEFAULT/foo' : value => $myvar }

If for any reason '<SERVICE DEFAULT>' turns out to be a valid value for
a specific parameter. One could by pass that doing the following :

sahara_config { 'DEFAULT/foo' : value => '<SERVICE DEFAULT>',
ensure_absent_val => 'foo' }

Change-Id: I06307555a70f3120b0840c6e7131172f79af7387
Depends-On: I0eeebde3aac2662cc7e69bfad7f8d2481463a218

commit_message:
neutron: add support for q-qos service

If q-qos is enabled in local.conf, then the following changes are
applied:

- qos is added to service_plugins list;
- qos is added to ml2 extension drivers list;
- qos is added to agent:extensions list.

Change-Id: I533fd9c717d47ae91e4941d3ed9e57ad802bc5e0
Partially-Implements: blueprint quantum-qos-api

Initial msync run for all Puppet OpenStack modules

* gitignore: just a sync between projects
* gemfile:

  - add a acceptance target

commit_message:
Move developer documentation to its own subtree

Prior to this change, all files at the root of the doc/source/ directory
were implied to be developer documentation. This commit moves them into
an explicit subdirectory, and re-words the section headings to be less
repetitive.

No changes to formatting or content were introduced.

Change-Id: Id00116ad2146f11df52dd8a331834719e1b8bd03
Closes-Bug: #1486789
(cherry picked from commit a6548e4f11a4b41b489a413ed31188bfb012388a)

commit_message:
Fix bad posargs for testr

If you run "tox -epy27 -- --concurrency=5" we should
add a space to correctly pass it down to testr or none
of the tests will run as posargs gets treated as part of
the test name pattern

Closes-Bug: #1487049
Change-Id: Ib8417daf666ee82354cb642bfd6289ec8382c438

commit_message:
Apache servers will not reporting version anymore

In order to make it more difficult to know which
httpd server is running, here is a change to 
reduce the ServerTokens OS to ServerTokens Prod
and the ServerSignature On to ServerSignature Off.

This removes ServerName and version report
on page footer and reduces the detail of the httpd
server running in the headers to "Apache". 

These options can be overwritten by an user variable

Change-Id: I1aaffaa3b6b7d6574aefac65b6027e62240a702b
Closes-Bug: #1484256
(cherry picked from commit 1d2c19d8409ad53bb5ca7bf180f433f05af91afe)

commit_message:
Initial msync run for all Puppet OpenStack modules

This patch is the initial modulesync run, it impacts:

* gitignore: just a sync between projects
* gemfile:
  - update and allow to setup facter version and gem source
  - split beaker gems with a dedicated group
  - switch to rspec-puppet 2.2.0
* rakefile:
  - use the new syntax for lint configuration
  - add a acceptance target
* acceptance:
  - sync nodesets
* spec: added rspec coverage report

Change-Id: I9a858f29644b3519d5b19fb9a0c45589968537ef

commit_message:
Initial msync run for all Puppet OpenStack modules

This patch is the initial modulesync run, it impacts:

* gitignore: just a sync between projects
* gemfile:
  - update and allow to setup facter version and gem source
  - split beaker gems with a dedicated group
  - switch to rspec-puppet 2.2.0
* rakefile:
  - use the new syntax for lint configuration
  - add a acceptance target
* acceptance:
  - sync nodesets
* spec: added rspec coverage report

Change-Id: I5fb7b79f14f52ff5598920ab8a2411aa02af6f72

commit_message:
Add to influx command's $PATH

The rpm and deb packages distributed by InfluxDB install to
/opt so to be friendly we stick that path on PATH. This is a bit
lame but will probably remove a significant number of questions
from people who are trying to run the influxdb tests.

Change-Id: I7d729c7d7abc2f4906789529891d03c686317a89

commit_message:
InfluxDB storage driver

This is a basic InfluxDB driver that covers the basic features of a
storage driver. It does not leverage any other feature such as
continuous query or cross aggregation metrics yet.
And does not reject measures too old according the archive policy.

It needs InfluxDB Server >= 0.9

Co-Author: Ilya Tyaptin <ityaptin@mirantis.com>
Co-Author: Mehdi Abaakouk <sileht@redhat.com>
Implements: influxdb-driver
Change-Id: I9754c8baff76f8712525e591d0a34571811b2a33

[{'number': 4, 'created': '2015-08-11 23:52:10.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/volume/drivers/pure.py', 'cinder/tests/unit/test_pure.py'], 'message': 'Enhance PureISCSIDriver multipath support

Add in support for alternative iSCSI portal information. We can also
return our whole list of connected ports for multipathing. This allows
us to not do any iSCSI discovery in the driver code since all portals
will be tried now in the connector code.

commit_message:
Enhance PureISCSIDriver multipath support

Add in support for alternative iSCSI portal information. We can also
return our whole list of connected ports for multipathing. This allows
us to not do any iSCSI discovery in the driver code since all portals
will be tried now in the connector code.

Change-Id: Iff18d1038aac3f9a234224c4dce5343dfae5e8c5
Implements: blueprint pure-iscsi-improved-multipath

commit_message:
Bump delorean to 2015-07-14 to fix openstack CLI

The `openstack` CLI won't run on overcloud, throwing this error:

[root@overcloud-controller-0 ~]# /usr/bin/openstack project list --quiet
--format csv --long
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/usr/bin/openstack", line 10, in <module>
    sys.exit(main())
  File "/usr/lib/python2.7/site-packages/openstackclient/shell.py", line
  375, in main
    return OpenStackShell().run(argv)
  File "/usr/lib/python2.7/site-packages/openstackclient/shell.py", line
  86, in __init__
    deferred_help=True)
TypeError: __init__() got an unexpected keyword argument 'deferred_help'

An updated python-cliff package from current delorean trunk fixes the
problem, so we need to bump the delorean URL.

Change-Id: I7c4899adaef1581345757bdc29623b80d6001688
Depends-On: I0dc419fc22536b403d2edbbe3fcb5ce4b6b4d3e8

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-08-20 10:44:00.000000000', 'files': ['lib/astute/server/server.rb'], 'message': 'Generate unique names for service queue

RabbitMQ supports such feature as temporary
queues with autogenerated names, it means that when you
define a queue, you leave the name empty, so RabbitMQ generates
a unique name with "amq.gen-" prefix, after fixing a bug [1]
with heartbeats, we got working reconnects in case of connectivity
issues. When reconnect happens, for queues with autogenerated
names RabbitMQ behaves strangely, it does not delete previous queues
but creates new one, so for a single worker there is old/not
used queue and the new one. When new message comes to exchange
it has 50% chance to get into working queue. If there more
reconnects happen, more dead queues are created and we have
less chance to get message in working queue.

In order to prevent that, each worker should have unique
name for its service queue, which it will use during worker's
life time. When reconnect happens, it will try to connect to
the same queue which was used before.

RabbitMQ version: 3.3.5
[1] https://bugs.launchpad.net/fuel/+bug/1483182

Change-Id: I6a92319af986ee2f76d07ce86d14a6875b836412
Closes-bug: #1485895
'}]
commit_message:
Generate unique names for service queue

RabbitMQ supports such feature as temporary
queues with autogenerated names, it means that when you
define a queue, you leave the name empty, so RabbitMQ generates
a unique name with "amq.gen-" prefix, after fixing a bug [1]
with heartbeats, we got working reconnects in case of connectivity
issues. When reconnect happens, for queues with autogenerated
names RabbitMQ behaves strangely, it does not delete previous queues
but creates new one, so for a single worker there is old/not
used queue and the new one. When new message comes to exchange
it has 50% chance to get into working queue. If there more
reconnects happen, more dead queues are created and we have
less chance to get message in working queue.

In order to prevent that, each worker should have unique
name for its service queue, which it will use during worker's
life time. When reconnect happens, it will try to connect to
the same queue which was used before.

RabbitMQ version: 3.3.5
[1] https://bugs.launchpad.net/fuel/+bug/1483182

Change-Id: I6a92319af986ee2f76d07ce86d14a6875b836412
Closes-bug: #1485895

commit_message:
Fix incorrect resource's information while describing

We can't get the resource'infos from db once the resource
is deleted. All information of a deleted resource come
from the initialization. So this change will modify some
infos when resource init:
1. set the action of resource to stack'action
2. set the created_time to stack's created_time
3. set the updated_time to stack's updated_time

Then the information will be reset for normal resources.

Change-Id: Iafdc99c572c5dab06bf1843842ed47554d6de128
Closes-Bug: #1480183

commit_message:
Introduce the key-manager:service-admin role

In Barbican, the admin role specifies a user that has complete
authority over resources within a project.  An admin for one
project should not have access to resources in a different project.
A project admin should not be able to affect service-wide resources.

With the implementation of the quotas blueprint, there is a need for
a new limited purpose role.  This role will be able to manage project
quotas, but will not have access to projects' stored keys and secrets.

This change request proposes the new role ("key-manager:service-admin")
that can be used for this purpose.

The changes are implemented in the default policy and will
give this new role access to set, read, and delete project quotas.  It
will also have access to the resources and actions available to "all_users".
The default policy grants no other permissions to this role.

Partially-implements: blueprint quota-support-on-barbican-resources
Change-Id: I67be5de62b508fdc88f5d29e69bfa6341d0487d1

The common practice of making nova-compute (with vmwareapi driver
chosen) HA is to have it run in active/passive mode controlled by
Pacemaker.  In that case Pacemaker can move nova-compute instance to
another host, should something happen to the original one, which
effectively will cause change of the IP address - thus, all cached
images will have to be re-downloaded again, despite the fact they are
still there in the datastore and still belong to this particular
nova-compute instance.

I02e758af19cf3a652a5c39d02904e73a1088fe60 made it possible to use the
`cache_prefix' config option to denote, which cache directory should
be used by a particular nova-compute instance. As long as we set the
same `cache_prefix' value for all nova-compute processes running in
active/passive mode, the cache directory will be the same on every
host.

Closes-Bug: #1482121

Change-Id: Id70dd29a757f41c9d02a3573c6581ba29e63b191
